Gauteng's Education MEC says all Grade 1 and 8 pupils who applied online for the 2022 school year have been placed. A total of 347,216 applications were received. The department's spokesperson Steve Mabona speaks more about this. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Department of Education says all Grade 1 and 8 pupils who applied online for the 2022 school year have been placed. The start of the academic year saw many frustrated parents line up outside schools to try to find a space for their children. WATCH: Parents frustrated over school placements Gauteng Education says a total of 347,216 applications were received. The department adds that it also received over 25,000 applications since it opened late submissions on 12 January 2022.